Git Help Commands
 git Help
 git help config
 git help Commands

Git Configuration Commands
 git config --global setting value

Configure User and Email
 git config --global user.name "Your Name"
 git config --global user.email "youremail@yourdomain.subdomain"
 git config --global --list

 cat ~/.gitconfig

Creating a Git Repo
 git init <repo-name>

 git status
 git add <File-name> / .
 git commit -m "<your commit msg here>"

 git commit -am "<your commit msg>" # for files being already tracked by git.

 git reset HEAD <file name> # To unstage file / unstaging changes.
 git checkout -- <filename> # Discard changes in working directory.

 git log # Shows commit history in reverse chronological order.
 git help log # to get help on command.

 git log --oneline --graph --decorate --color

 git rm <filename> # To remove a file from git.

 git add -u # if a file is deleted outside git and is to be committed.

 git mv <sourcefile> <dest. file> # for moving / renaming files in git.

 git add -u # If files are moved / renamed outside of git. and the chg needs to be committed.

 # Ignoring files with git , it should contain 1 pattern per line.

 vim .gitignore # i.e. *.log

 git add -u # The u parameter will recursively update git's staging area regarding deleted
 #moved files outside of git.

# working with remote branch.

 ssh-keygen -t rsa -C "your.name@yourdomain.com" # generate ssh key for github.

 ssh -T git@github.com

 git remote add origin <Your git repo url here>
 git push -u origin master
 git remote -v # shows remote url

 git pull # Always do a pull before pushing in remote branch.
 
